Description: A sealing for an unknown object, probably a document: two adjacent impressions from intaglio gems, one complete with a bust of a man to right, the other partially surviving, perhaps the head of a woman to right, with only the hair and its bun drawn back. Unfired pale yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD, the gem with the man perhaps of a century earlier.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3643)
